    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="1292"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1292">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123E16/92a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                    <gloss type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the Minister in Roumania, Servia, and Bulgaria</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-18T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1915, 6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>166. Department’s 165, 16th,<note n="1" xml:id="d1292fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    intended that <persName corresp="#p_EL1">Einstein</persName>, now presumably
                    awaiting instructions Bucharest should proceed to Sofia if the Bulgarian
                    Government has expressed its willingness to receive him in capacity of Chargé
                    d’Affaires and that on his arrival in Sofia he will assume charge of British
                    interests.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
